dplyr has 5 verbs: filter, select, mutate, arrange, summarise

filter: Keep rows matching criteria

## mutate: Add new variables
# create a new variable Speed (in mph)

flights <- flights %>% mutate(Speed = Distance/AirTime*60)

summarise: Reduce variables to values

# calculate the average arrival delay for each  flight carrier

flights %>%
  group_by(UniqueCarrier) %>%
  summarise(avg_delay = mean(ArrDelay, na.rm=TRUE))

# calculate the percentage of flights cancelled or diverted, for each destination

# helper function n(), distinct_n()
# for each day of the year, count the total number of flights and sort in descending order
flights %>%
  group_by(Month, DayofMonth) %>%
  summarise(flight_count=n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(flight_count))
